</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR162:v98#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR162"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              162-&#xA;                AMENDED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Amended
               IN </span><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Senate
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">June 04, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 162</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member<font color="#B30000"><strike> Gallagher</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> </i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Hadwick</i></font><br/>(Principal coauthor: Senator Dahle)<br/><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(Coauthor: Assembly Member Macedo)<br/></i></font></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>March 18, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;">Relative to the Congressman Doug LaMalfa Memorial Highway. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 162, as amended, <font color="#B30000"><strike><caml:Legislator><caml:Name>Gallagher</caml:Name></caml:Legislator></strike></font>&nbsp;<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Hadwick.
                          </i></font>Congressman Doug LaMalfa Memorial Highway.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would designate a specified portion of State Route 99 in the County of Butte as the Congressman Doug LaMalfa Memorial Highway. The measure would request that the Department of Transportation determine the cost of appropriate signs showing this special designation and, upon receiving donations from nonstate sources sufficient to cover the cost, to erect those signs.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_EDFBF78A-092B-4D67-8757-921E7C3A13EE"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, On July 2, 1960, Douglas “Doug” LaMalfa was born in Oroville, California; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A8F638D1-929B-4618-B4C3-3D0A1B82ECCC"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, In 1978, Mr. LaMalfa graduated from Biggs High School and, in 1982, he received his bachelor’s degree in agricultural business from the California Polytechnic State University, San Luis Obispo; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_7DB60A75-9AB6-4005-B9DE-C039D73BEDD6"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Mr. LaMalfa was a fourth-generation rice farmer and businessman; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_80A72971-390C-4F14-B50A-BC92A71EDE01"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, In 2002, Mr. LaMalfa successfully ran for the California State Assembly, beginning his long tenure of public service; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_7F1A510E-56BC-44F8-891B-AF3DB970914C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Mr. LaMalfa served in the California State Assembly and California State Senate before being elected in 2012 to the United States House of Representatives; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_8C40760C-881D-466B-8B40-E73BD0428F9B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, From 2013 to 2026, inclusive, Congressman LaMalfa served California’s First Congressional District and was a strong advocate for northern California’s agriculture- and natural resources-based economy; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_87E9D2C5-D2BB-4FD8-AB4E-EF2EA3A23C3F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Congressman LaMalfa was unanimously elected as chairman of the Congressional Western Caucus, one of the largest membership organizations in Congress, and he fought for<font color="#B30000"><strike> farms, businesses,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> businesses, farms,</i></font> and rural priorities; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_3AD59755-4D55-49C7-BC1B-E108EED982ED"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Congressman LaMalfa was deeply rooted in his faith and values, and he led with humility, kindness, and authenticity; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_030E687B-5162-4D31-A25C-85D231D9926A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Congressman LaMalfa was a devoted husband, father, and grandfather, and he and his wife, Jill, raised their four children on their family farm in Richvale, California, teaching them to work hard and value community; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_17E7CCA5-ACCF-4847-ACE6-67A685D17315"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, On January 6, 2026, Congressman LaMalfa tragically passed away, and he left behind his wife, Jill, their four children, Kyle, Allison, Sophia, and Natalie, his grandchild, two sisters, and a host of cousins, extended family, and dear friends; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_20810DCA-D95F-4764-90D3-752ABD43FCB2"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Congressman LaMalfa was known and loved throughout his community, and he will be dearly missed by his family, friends, colleagues, and constituents; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_753FAF49-FC95-4672-A296-04456EBCE129"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature hereby designates the segment of State Route 99 from Cottonwood Creek BB12-0206, at postmile 15.374, to Dry Creek 12 123, at postmile 20.598, in the County of Butte as the Congressman Doug LaMalfa Memorial Highway; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_7C3CFFC9-9679-440F-8E60-C55393220025"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Department of Transportation is requested to determine the cost of appropriate signs, consistent with the signing requirements for the state highway system, showing this special designation and, upon receiving donations from nonstate sources sufficient to cover the cost, to erect those signs; and be it further </div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_976F2534-A79F-4228-8EF9-46D477AE3258"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the Director of Transportation and to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
